                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.24/155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lay</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 20, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>26. Your 62, April 19, noon. You may say to President Mejia Colindres that
                    although the Government of the United States will not sell a bombing airplane to
                    the Government of Honduras, it will be disposed upon receipt of application to
                    grant a license for the export of such military aircraft acquired from
                    commercial sources and consigned to the Government of Honduras. However it would
                    be opposed to American citizens operating it in connection with civil
                    disturbances and carrying on bombing operations. Keep Department informed on
                    this score as it will want to make a statement regarding Americans who undertake
                    such operations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
